<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<!DOCTYPE concept PUBLIC "-//OASIS//DTD DITA Concept//EN" "concept.dtd" []>
<concept xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" id="topicref" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="urn:oasis:names:tc:dita:xsd:concept.xsd:1.1">
  <title>Topicref</title>
  <conbody>
    <p id="topicref"><term>Topicref</term><indexterm>topicref</indexterm>, or<term> topic reference</term><indexterm> topic reference</indexterm>, is a reference from within a <xref href="dita-maps-serna-free.xml">map</xref> to an external topic, DITA document  or non-DITA document.</p>
    <p>Topicrefs are characterized by the following:</p>
    <p><ul>
        <li>
          <p><b>Target location</b></p>
          <p><term>Topicrefs</term> can link to:<ol>
              <li>
                <p>External topics</p>
              </li>
              <li>
                <p>DITA documents</p>
              </li>
              <li>
                <p>Non-DITA documents</p>
              </li>
            </ol></p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p><b>Attributes</b></p>
          <p conref="xref.xml#xref/href-attribute"/>
          <p conref="xref.xml#xref/format-attribute"/>
          <p conref="xref.xml#xref/scope-attribute"/>
          <p conref="related-link.xml#related-link/type-attribute"/>
          <p>The <codeph>collection-type</codeph> attribute  describes how topicrefs relate to each other: choice, family, sequence, unordered. </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p><b>Views of topicref</b></p>
          <p>Topicrefs can be displayed two ways: either unresolved (as links) or as resolved content of referenced documents. For more information, see <xref href="dita-maps-xslt-parameter-sets-serna-free.xml"/>.</p>
          <fig>
            <title>Unresolved and resolved views of topicrefs in Serna.</title>
            <image href="resolved-and-unresolved-views-of-topicref.png" align="center"/>
          </fig>
        </li>
      </ul></p>
  </conbody>
</concept>
